Federal health officials say 106 passengers and six crew members aboard the Celebrity Infinity cruise ship were sickened by the gastrointestinal illness norovirus
The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention -LRB- CDC -RRB- said in
Monday news release there were 2117 total passengers on the ship and 964 total crew members
The agency said the main symptoms for those affected were diarrhea and throwing up
The Celebrity website says the ship regularly travels through the Panama Canal and to Alaska
